Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Filter
    Abstract class to for specific filters to extend, and override the run method
    FirstFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for scanning in a text file and adding the contents to the output buffer
    FrameBuilderFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings of base pairs, and outputting all possible frames of base pairs for the rest of the filters to leverage
    GapFinderFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings of base pairs, whitespace, and gap indicators and outputting the split reads as strings
    LastFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings to be print to the command line
    MultithreadingDriver
    Instantiates 7 Runable Filters, ArrayBlockQueue buffers to transfer strings between the filters, and places all Filters in a ThreadPool to be managed by an ExecutorService.
    ORFFinderFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings of base pairs, and outputting all possible frames of base pairs for the rest of the filters to leverage
    ReverseComplementorFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings of base pairs, and outputting the original string, and the reverse complement of the string
    TranslatorFilter
    Extends abstract class Filter, and contains the specific code for inputting strings of base pairs, and converting those strings to amino acid characters which are output
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Codon
    The Codons used in genomics, containing all 22 amino acid abbreviations, and base pair conversions.
